Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.68,0:47:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The progression spiritual spiritually\Nthrough meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.92,0:48:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,has classically been likened to\Nrenunciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.59,0:48:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case the renunciation is mental\Nrather than a social lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.11,0:48:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So that all all spiritual work in a way\Nis a renunciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.64,0:48:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, we've talked in previous\Ntalks about transcending the opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.11,0:48:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The polarity of the opposites is an\Nillusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.52,0:48:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And one doesn't have to choose between\Nopposites. One merely sees the opposite,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.92,0:48:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what seems like in the opposite\Ndirection as an alternate.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.92,0:48:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,One then refuses the alternate and\Nmerely chooses the positive. So you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.55,0:48:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to be against\Nwhat is seen to be the negative. You
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.44,0:48:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to hate sin and get out there\Nand fight sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.07,0:48:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You just choose virtue, right? Choose.\NSo you choose the positive rather than
